<paragraph id="8BAA6179DF1EFFE01EE28CBB2E8AFB65" blockId="25.[143,241,1156,1180]" box="[143,241,1156,1180]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430">
<emphasis id="B961BD6BDF1EFFE01EE28CBB2E8AFB65" box="[143,241,1156,1180]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA6179DF1EFFE01EE28C942FDAFABA" blockId="25.[143,1104,1195,1443]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430">This species is well characterized by an unusual sexual dimorphism in colouration: pronotum is fulvous with a dark central stripe; elytron is completely blue in female, and is fulvous with a broad lateral dark violaceous stripe in male. Moreover, the elytra have regular rows of punctures. According to the original description, the aedeagal apex is long and narrow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA6179DF1EFFE01ED78D732F08FA5A" blockId="25.[143,1104,1195,1443]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430">
We examined the 
<typeStatus id="54AEDFDBDF1EFFE01FE08D742F8AFA9A" box="[397,497,1355,1379]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D13AAF0DF1EFFE01C5C8D732CAEFA9D" box="[561,725,1356,1380]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">two paratypes</specimenCount>
, all are males. 
<location id="8ECA37A2DF1EFFE01DE78D742DCDFA9A" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03BCD06FDF1EFFE01FCB8A622F08FA5A:8ECA37A2DF1EFFE01DE78D742DCDFA9A" box="[906,950,1355,1379]" name="The" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430">The</location>
type locality of the 
<typeStatus id="54AEDFDBDF1EFFE01E8C8D542F3EFA7A" box="[225,325,1387,1411]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1430">holotype</typeStatus>
is “Weibaoshan mts.”, which differs from the original description “Meibaoshan mts.”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
